verses.text: Give unto the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*, O ye mighty, give unto the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*glory and strength.
Give unto the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*the glory due unto his name; worship the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*in the beauty of holiness.
The voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*isupon the waters: the God of glory thundereth: the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*isupon many waters.
The voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*ispowerful; the voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*isfull of majesty.
The voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*breaketh the cedars; yea, the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*breaketh the cedars of Lebanon.
He maketh them also to skip like a calf; Lebanon and Sirion like a young unicorn.
The voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*divideth the flames of fire.
The voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*shaketh the wilderness; the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*shaketh the wilderness of Kadesh.
The voice of the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*maketh the hinds to calve, and discovereth the forests: and in his temple doth every one speak of hisglory.
The \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*sitteth upon the flood; yea, the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*sitteth King for ever.
The \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*will give strength unto his people; the \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*will bless his people with peace.
